{"atom_id":"ig34_p0103_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":103,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In this rheumatoid arthritis (RA) study, the sponsor collected medications using the category \"Prior RA Medications\", then collected information on whether the subject had received certain medication classes, represented as subcategories. If a subject did receive medications in a subcategory, information about those medications was collected. This example shows data for 2 subjects who received prior RA medications. It includes data only about their prior disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs (DMARDs); information about other kinds of prior RA medications is not included.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10+option_E_rerun_p103","ts":"2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
